and has never exhibited behavior
even remotely aggressive.

27:18.530 --> 27:20.830
        Do you think
        I’m making it up?
Of course not.

27:20.830 --> 27:23.240
But yesterday,
a patient in your care

27:23.240 --> 27:25.830
killed herself brutally
in front of you.

27:26.670 --> 27:28.640
Is it possible,
when you presumed

27:28.640 --> 27:30.610
that Carl Renken
was a danger to himself,

27:30.610 --> 27:32.970
that that’s what your mind
was reacting to?

27:36.320 --> 27:40.250
I suppose
I could’ve misinterpreted
the situation and overreacted.

27:43.020 --> 27:44.260
Okay.

27:44.260 --> 27:46.890
So, here’s what’s gonna happen.

27:47.990 --> 27:50.060
You’re gonna take
a paid week off.

27:50.060 --> 27:51.930
Morgan,
that’s really not necessary.

27:51.930 --> 27:55.400
You’ve been working
80-hour weeks for months.

27:55.400 --> 27:58.230
I’m concerned
that you haven’t been sleeping.

27:58.230 --> 28:02.070
We can’t help these patients
unless we have
our own mental health in check.

28:02.070 --> 28:04.000
And it’s in
the unit’s best interest

28:04.000 --> 28:06.200
if you just take a week
and clear your head.

28:06.200 --> 28:09.480
Just do what you gotta do
and come back focused, okay?

31:22.510 --> 31:23.840
Fuck!

32:33.980 --> 32:37.240
Hello?
This is First Line Security.

32:37.240 --> 32:39.620
May I have your name
and the passcode?

32:39.620 --> 32:41.620
Uh, Rose Cotter.

32:41.620 --> 32:43.220
Um, "Acapulco."

32:43.220 --> 32:44.990
Ma’am, we’ve detected
a door alarm.

32:44.990 --> 32:48.830
Yeah, uh, the--
the back door
of my house is open.

32:48.830 --> 32:50.760
Are you alone
in the house, ma’am?

32:51.220 --> 32:52.520
Yes.

32:52.520 --> 32:53.960
Are you sure?

32:55.670 --> 32:59.710
           What?
Are you sure you haven’t
let something inside, Rose?

33:02.330 --> 33:04.040
Look behind you.

33:34.430 --> 33:35.710
Shit.

33:43.380 --> 33:44.720
Hello?

33:44.720 --> 33:46.310
This is First Line Security.

33:46.310 --> 33:48.480
May I have your name
and the passcode?

34:09.400 --> 34:11.810
We did a full sweep
inside and out.
It’s all clear.

34:12.600 --> 34:14.949
Um, what about the back door?

34:14.949 --> 34:18.150
Is it possible
it wasn’t fully latched
last time it was closed?

34:19.610 --> 34:21.850
I-- I don’t know.
Maybe.

34:21.850 --> 34:23.219
Hey,
I wouldn’t worry about it.

34:23.219 --> 34:25.889
These false alarms
happen all the time.

34:25.889 --> 34:28.489
If anything else comes up,
you can give us a call.

34:29.360 --> 34:30.489
Okay.

34:31.420 --> 34:32.900
Evening, sir.

34:32.900 --> 34:35.489
Um, evening.

34:39.130 --> 34:40.500
What happened?

34:43.940 --> 34:45.239
Mustache?

34:46.909 --> 34:48.750
Mustache.

34:48.750 --> 34:52.280
So, is there a reason
you set the alarm?

34:52.280 --> 34:53.179
Uh--

34:54.150 --> 34:56.050
I literally
don’t remember doing it.

34:56.050 --> 34:59.150
I must have just, like,
set it by accident or something.

35:00.790 --> 35:02.190
By accident?

35:03.760 --> 35:05.160
Sorry. Sorry.

35:05.160 --> 35:07.330
My head has just been
in this, like,

35:07.330 --> 35:10.300
foggy, creepy,
spacey place all day.

35:10.300 --> 35:13.330
And there was
this weird incident
at work and then--

35:13.330 --> 35:15.710
and then my boss
is making me take a--

35:19.600 --> 35:22.010
Sorry.

35:22.010 --> 35:25.020
Everything is okay.
Are you sure?

35:25.020 --> 35:28.080
No, no, I’m fine.
I was just venting.

35:29.990 --> 35:31.350
Okay.

35:36.290 --> 35:38.060
Can you see
if you can find Mustache?

35:38.060 --> 35:40.060
I haven’t seen him
anywhere at all.

35:40.060 --> 35:41.300
Yeah.

35:47.810 --> 35:50.110
Rose, did you
break another glass?

35:54.850 --> 35:56.210
Mustache?

35:59.640 --> 36:01.080
Come on, kitty.

36:03.650 --> 36:05.790
Please. Please.

36:09.590 --> 36:10.960
Mustache.

37:06.510 --> 37:09.250
It looks like people.
It looks like different people.

37:09.250 --> 37:11.750
Sometimes it pretends
to be someone that I know.

37:11.750 --> 37:14.690
Sometimes it’s
a random stranger.
Sometimes--

37:14.690 --> 37:17.290
Sometimes it looks like
my grandfather

37:17.290 --> 37:20.160
who died in front of me
when I was seven.

37:20.160 --> 37:22.730
But it’s all the same thing.
It--

37:22.730 --> 37:25.470
It’s smiling at me,
but not a friendly smile.

37:25.470 --> 37:27.760
It’s the worst smile
I’ve ever seen in my life.

37:27.760 --> 37:30.570
And whenever I see it,
I just get
this god-awful feeling

37:30.570 --> 37:33.800
like something really terrible
is gonna happen.

37:35.110 --> 37:37.950
Oh, my God! No! No!

37:37.950 --> 37:40.780
No! It’s here! Please!

37:40.780 --> 37:43.650
Get away! Please! No!

37:45.250 --> 37:47.490
       I-- I have
a patient emergency in eval 2.

37:47.490 --> 37:50.330
I need staff here now. Hurry.

37:52.060 --> 37:53.360
Laura?

38:04.240 --> 38:05.440
Laura?

38:16.580 --> 38:18.450
Laura?

38:18.450 --> 38:20.720
Rose.

38:28.630 --> 38:30.170
Laura?

38:38.980 --> 38:40.510
Rose!

38:51.680 --> 38:53.090
Rose?

38:53.090 --> 38:55.850
Whoa! Oh, my God! Rose!
Rose! Whoa, whoa!

38:55.850 --> 38:58.330
What the fuck?
Rose, put the knife down!

39:02.530 --> 39:03.560
Rose!

39:21.990 --> 39:23.220
Hi.

39:24.880 --> 39:26.260
Rose?

39:27.650 --> 39:29.330
This is a surprise.

39:31.920 --> 39:34.730
It wasn’t so much the blood.

39:34.730 --> 39:36.100
It was, um...

39:37.200 --> 39:39.070
her face.

39:39.070 --> 39:41.010
The look that she had.

39:42.110 --> 39:43.500
How did it
make you feel?

39:45.210 --> 39:46.280
Uh--

39:46.840 --> 39:48.670
Terrified, obviously.

39:50.840 --> 39:51.940
Um--

39:52.880 --> 39:54.450
Vulnerable.

39:54.940 --> 39:56.290
Guilty.

39:56.680 --> 39:57.820
Guilty?

39:58.550 --> 40:00.420
Well, she was my patient.

40:00.420 --> 40:04.590
She was a disturbed young woman
you only met for ten minutes.

40:04.590 --> 40:06.630
Yeah. I just--

40:08.070 --> 40:09.830
I just feel like
I’ve gotten stuck on it.

40:09.830 --> 40:12.340
I can’t, you know,
get it out of my head.

40:12.340 --> 40:16.140
Have you considered
the reason you feel stuck

40:16.140 --> 40:18.900
could actually be more about
your mother’s suicide?

40:23.580 --> 40:25.650
Do you still blame yourself?

40:27.450 --> 40:29.150
That--

40:29.150 --> 40:30.910
I’m really not trying
to relitigate

40:30.910 --> 40:33.850
that part of my life
right now. So...

40:35.420 --> 40:37.460
What would you like
to talk about?

40:38.790 --> 40:44.570
I was hoping that I could get
a script for Risperdal.

40:50.740 --> 40:52.210
Ever since that...

40:54.150 --> 40:56.010
patient, I’ve been, um...

40:57.680 --> 40:59.680
seeing things

41:00.610 --> 41:02.390
and hearing things.

41:03.750 --> 41:06.690
I’m sure it’s just a symptom
of post-trauma.

41:06.690 --> 41:09.260
Let’s avoid
any self-diagnosis.

41:10.760 --> 41:13.130
What is it you’ve been seeing
and hearing?

41:16.760 --> 41:19.630
Echoes of what happened
with my patient.

41:19.630 --> 41:22.210
You know,
just fleeting moments

41:22.210 --> 41:24.570
of stress-induced
hallucinations.

41:25.970 --> 41:29.940
But when they’re happening,
they feel so...

41:31.180 --> 41:35.190
corporeal and unsettling.

41:37.010 --> 41:40.620
Rose, from where I’m sitting,
you don’t seem delusional
or disordered to me.

41:41.490 --> 41:43.490
And certainly not psychotic.

41:43.490 --> 41:46.400
It’s my impression
 this experience
with your patient

41:46.400 --> 41:47.990
triggered old anxieties

41:47.990 --> 41:50.300
compounded
with too much stress,
not enough sleep.

41:50.300 --> 41:54.110
You have wounds
that have never fully healed.

41:56.140 --> 41:59.440
And it is possible
they never will completely.
That’s the nature of trauma.

41:59.440 --> 42:02.910
But you can learn
to get control over it.

42:04.320 --> 42:07.350
Have you been continuing
to see patients

42:07.350 --> 42:09.190
while you’ve been coping
with all this?

42:09.190 --> 42:13.130
           No. I’m just taking
           a short hiatus.
Good.

42:14.560 --> 42:16.200
If you want my advice,

42:16.200 --> 42:17.920
use this time
to do something different.

42:17.920 --> 42:20.330
Anything that will
take your mind off

42:20.330 --> 42:22.600
the triggers
that are causing you stress.

42:22.600 --> 42:26.140
I also think
it would be helpful

42:27.240 --> 42:29.800
if we resumed
our regular sessions again.

42:34.740 --> 42:36.110
Sure.

42:40.880 --> 42:43.850
And what about the Risperdal?
Just-- You know.

42:43.850 --> 42:47.620
Let’s talk again next week
before we consider
any medication.

42:49.590 --> 42:52.020
In the meantime,
you can always call me.

42:55.760 --> 42:57.090
Sure.

43:28.760 --> 43:32.440
No, I asked you for
a white wine spritzer. Jesus.

43:33.830 --> 43:36.470
    Oh, my God. You made it.
Hi. Surprise.

43:36.470 --> 43:38.040
Come on in. Come on in.
Oh.

43:38.870 --> 43:40.910
I thought you had to work?

43:40.910 --> 43:43.510
Oh, I decided
to take the afternoon...
 I’ll take that.

43:43.510 --> 43:45.220
Hey, Greg.
What are you doing?

43:45.220 --> 43:47.650
I told you
not to take those out yet.
Mmm, mmm.

43:47.650 --> 43:49.320
Geez.

43:49.320 --> 43:51.260
Uh, ladies,
I have to go corral
my dipshit husband.

43:51.260 --> 43:54.080
Would one of you
please show my sister
to the adult refreshments?

43:54.080 --> 43:56.530
Sure. We have a stash
in the kitchen. Come on.

43:56.530 --> 43:58.690
Wait.
You’re that therapist, right?

43:58.690 --> 43:59.990
Yes, I-- I am.

43:59.990 --> 44:01.830
Oh! Fantastic.
Can I ask for advice?

44:01.830 --> 44:16.210
♪

44:42.900 --> 44:45.870
So cool.

44:45.870 --> 44:49.110
Harper.
Harper’s mom.

44:54.140 --> 44:56.080
Ooh, that one’s
from Aunt Rose.

44:58.920 --> 45:00.120
Open it!

45:01.150 --> 45:02.630
Rip it open!

45:18.000 --> 45:19.350
What’d you get,
sweetheart?

45:33.850 --> 45:35.560
No. No.

45:35.560 --> 45:39.090
Oh, my God.
No, no. Mustache.

45:41.960 --> 45:44.290
What the hell is wrong
with you?

45:44.290 --> 45:46.000
This can’t be happening.

45:50.870 --> 45:54.410
No. No, no.
No, I promise you,
this wasn’t me.

45:54.410 --> 45:57.910
It wasn’t.
It wasn’t me, I swear.

45:57.910 --> 46:00.980
You have to--
You guys have to
believe me, please.

46:00.980 --> 46:04.150
Somebody
please fucking believe me.

46:13.030 --> 46:17.100
What the fuck are you?
Leave me the fuck alone!

46:17.100 --> 46:20.260
You see her.
You have to see her.

46:20.260 --> 46:23.270
Please, Holly,
tell me that you see somebody.

46:23.270 --> 46:24.480
Please.

46:32.780 --> 46:34.390
Oh, my God.
Oh, God.

46:55.870 --> 46:57.640
Hey, Rose.

46:58.330 --> 46:59.340
Fuck.

47:00.940 --> 47:02.580
I heard you were brought
into the ER.

47:02.580 --> 47:04.650
I wanted to come check on you.
How’re you doing?

47:05.520 --> 47:07.150
Fine.

47:07.150 --> 47:09.950
It was just an accident.
Thank you.

47:09.950 --> 47:14.250
Yeah. They--
They said that you had
had a anxiety attack.

47:15.530 --> 47:17.600
Rose, I’ll be honest with you,
I’m-- I’m concerned.

47:17.600 --> 47:19.160
And I-- I mean this
as your friend,

47:19.160 --> 47:21.390
but I really think
you should speak
to someone.

47:21.390 --> 47:23.730
Are you seeing anybody
professionally right now?

47:29.900 --> 47:31.680
Rose, are you listening?

47:56.390 --> 47:57.500
Wait.

47:58.390 --> 48:00.330
I need to tell you something,

48:00.330 --> 48:06.240
and I need you to know
that I’m not crazy, okay?

48:06.840 --> 48:09.110
Okay.

48:10.040 --> 48:11.180
Um--

48:12.310 --> 48:16.590
Something is happening to me.

48:20.450 --> 48:23.350
And it’s gonna be really hard
for you to believe.

48:26.290 --> 48:28.420
Maybe we should
just go inside.

48:28.420 --> 48:31.640
No, wait. Just listen to me!
Sorry. Sorry.

48:32.430 --> 48:33.940
I’m really sorry.

48:34.430 --> 48:35.840
Okay, um--

48:37.770 --> 48:39.510
Something is threatening me.

48:40.470 --> 48:45.950
Some kind of a evil spirit,
or energy.

48:45.950 --> 48:50.720
I-- I don’t really know
what it is, but--

48:50.720 --> 48:54.190
but I think that it--
it killed my patient.

48:54.190 --> 48:58.630
Because she described
experiencing the same thing
before she died.

48:58.630 --> 49:02.570
And now it’s somehow
attached itself to me.

49:04.030 --> 49:05.200
And...

49:06.500 --> 49:07.800
I’m just really scared

49:07.800 --> 49:10.500
that something bad
is going to happen.

49:16.680 --> 49:18.780
I really need you
to say something.

49:19.820 --> 49:21.690
What do you want me to say?

49:26.190 --> 49:27.630
I want you to believe me.

49:27.630 --> 49:29.830
Rose, you’re talking about
a fucking ghost.

49:29.830 --> 49:31.860
No, no, no. It’s not--

49:31.860 --> 49:33.320
It’s not a ghost.

49:34.190 --> 49:36.000
It’s something else.

49:36.000 --> 49:37.330
Okay.

49:41.000 --> 49:42.430
I’m sorry.

49:43.500 --> 49:44.640
I can’t.

49:45.610 --> 49:47.370
I cannot fucking do this
right now.

49:47.370 --> 49:49.010
No. Trevor.

49:49.010 --> 49:51.240
Whoa, whoa, wait.
   No, no, no.
Don’t walk away.

49:52.510 --> 49:53.950
I need you--

49:53.950 --> 49:55.310
You’re not listening
to what I am saying.

49:55.310 --> 49:57.220
Okay, Rose.

49:57.220 --> 50:01.520
What the fuck am I
supposed to say to respond
to this right now?

50:01.520 --> 50:04.060
Do you hear yourself?
I mean, Jesus Christ.
You sound crazy.

50:04.060 --> 50:05.900
I am not crazy!

50:05.900 --> 50:07.770
Sorry. Sorry.

50:08.630 --> 50:10.490
But it’s genetic,
isn’t it?

50:11.530 --> 50:12.900
What?

50:14.070 --> 50:15.500
Mental illness.

50:16.470 --> 50:18.570
You can inherit it
from a parent.

50:18.570 --> 50:19.710
I looked it up.

50:19.710 --> 50:21.240
Why would you
look that up?

50:22.210 --> 50:24.880
Because...
I wanted to know

50:24.880 --> 50:28.210
what I was potentially
hitching my entire life to.

50:29.550 --> 50:31.420
Is that
so fucking unfair?

50:34.090 --> 50:35.630
I’m going in the house.

50:35.630 --> 50:38.060
No, no, no.
Please, Trevor.
I’m in danger!

50:38.060 --> 50:39.230
Rose.

50:40.030 --> 50:42.100
Did you kill Mustache?
N-- No!

50:42.100 --> 50:45.870
No! That was not--
That was not me.

50:45.870 --> 50:49.100
Then tell me,
what happened to him?

50:50.680 --> 50:53.040
It was the thing.

50:54.210 --> 50:56.210
Trevor, please.

50:56.210 --> 50:58.080
Please. Please.

50:59.280 --> 51:01.380
Please. Please.

52:16.060 --> 52:17.730
Rose.

52:26.840 --> 52:28.170
Come here.

52:57.800 --> 52:58.940
Rose.

53:01.840 --> 53:03.200
Baby...

53:04.240 --> 53:07.080
Please. Help me.

53:08.440 --> 53:11.510
  Mommy made a mistake.
No, no, no.

53:14.180 --> 53:15.580
No, no, no.

53:18.620 --> 53:19.960
Rose!

53:19.960 --> 53:21.260
Look where you’re going!

53:21.260 --> 53:23.620
Are you crazy?
Sorry. I’m sorry.

53:46.380 --> 53:47.680
Mrs. Muñoz?

53:50.580 --> 53:52.220
At first,

53:52.220 --> 53:54.520
I noticed
small changes in him.

53:57.290 --> 53:59.760
Then it all happened so fast.

54:01.630 --> 54:03.200
He was on edge.

54:04.000 --> 54:05.460
Paranoid.

54:07.100 --> 54:10.470
He would wake up
in the middle of the night,
screaming.

54:12.640 --> 54:14.880
I’d never heard him
scream before.

54:17.340 --> 54:20.350
Then he just
stopped sleeping altogether.

54:23.280 --> 54:26.820
I would catch him having
these conversations
with himself.

54:26.820 --> 54:28.490
He was seeing things.

54:29.390 --> 54:30.720
Doing strange things

54:30.720 --> 54:32.930
that he didn’t even
seem to remember.

54:33.660 --> 54:35.560
Then one morning he was gone.

54:37.100 --> 54:41.240
That night, the police called
and told me he was dead.

54:44.830 --> 54:46.800
They asked me
to identify his body.

54:47.770 --> 54:50.050
His face.

54:52.210 --> 54:54.450
Twenty-five years of marriage,

54:54.450 --> 54:57.380
and that’s what I have left
to remember him.

55:01.120 --> 55:03.090
I’m so sorry.

55:13.970 --> 55:19.210
Did Gabriel ever describe
the things that he was seeing?

55:23.810 --> 55:25.120
I’ll show you.

55:36.820 --> 55:38.820
I should take it all down,

55:39.820 --> 55:41.890
but I can’t stand
being in here.

56:00.680 --> 56:03.420
This is what Gabriel said
he saw.

56:11.690 --> 56:15.760
He kept saying it was trying
to get inside of him.

56:18.230 --> 56:20.930
That is Gabriel’s brother.

56:20.930 --> 56:24.570
He died in an accident
20 years ago.

56:24.570 --> 56:27.640
Gabriel never got over it.

56:27.640 --> 56:29.770
How long
had this been going on?

56:29.770 --> 56:33.150
Ever since he got back
from that damn conference
he would go to every year.

56:34.940 --> 56:38.220
It was because he saw
that awful woman kill herself.

56:39.920 --> 56:41.690
But no one
reports on that.

56:44.130 --> 56:47.130
He watched someone
die by suicide?

56:48.730 --> 56:49.790
Yes.

56:50.430 --> 56:51.560
I assumed you knew this.

56:51.560 --> 56:53.010
What was her name?

56:54.300 --> 56:56.730
I don’t remember.
I’d have to find it.

56:59.900 --> 57:01.050
Um--

57:01.970 --> 57:04.640
Did-- Did he ever, um...

57:06.780 --> 57:08.650
say why
all of this was happening?

57:08.650 --> 57:12.120
Did he find any explanation
in all of this?

57:14.060 --> 57:15.620
What kind of reporter
are you?

57:15.620 --> 57:20.160
Mrs. Muñoz,
your husband was not insane.

57:20.160 --> 57:23.730
The things that he was seeing,
they’re real. I’ve seen them.

57:23.730 --> 57:26.630
What are you,
a fucking nutcase?

57:26.630 --> 57:28.300
              What?
Some kind of
morbid fanatic?

57:28.300 --> 57:30.110
How fucking dare you?

57:30.110 --> 57:31.770
No, please. Please.

57:31.770 --> 57:34.340
What happened
to your husband
is happening to me.

57:34.340 --> 57:36.580
Out of my house.
I want you
out of my house, now.

57:36.580 --> 57:38.970
 Just please give me the name.
Please, just give me the name!

57:38.970 --> 57:41.520
Get the fuck
out of my house!

58:17.490 --> 58:19.220
Oh, fuck. Shit.

58:31.990 --> 58:33.240
Yeah?

58:39.710 --> 58:40.900
Hey.

58:47.550 --> 58:48.980
Come on in.

59:02.830 --> 59:06.270
Finally got rid of
that ugly yellow couch.

59:07.440 --> 59:08.770
Uh-huh.

59:09.410 --> 59:11.510
So, uh, what’s up?

59:12.610 --> 59:14.670
I assume you’re not here
to catch up

59:14.670 --> 59:17.680
considering the cold shoulder
the other day.

59:19.480 --> 59:21.810
   I need a favor.

59:21.810 --> 59:24.190
I need you to not ask
